        <div id="further-information">
            <div class="furthur-information-block">
                <div class="furthur-information-block-top"></div>
                <div class="furthur-information-block-mid">
                    <div class="block">
                        <h3>Bug tracking</h3>
                        <h4>Sharing code means sharing bugs.</h4>
                        <p class="screen-holder">
                            <img src="images/home/screens/bugs.jpg" alt="Bug tracking" />
                        </p>
                        <p>In the free software world, the same code is used by many different communities. Launchpad helps you work with different groups affected by the same bug. By sharing bug reports, statuses, patches and comments you can have a conversation across project boundaries to develop a fix. Even where the bug is tracked in different places with different tools - such as in Bugzilla or Trac - Launchpad can import comments and status information directly into your bug report.
                        </p>
                        <ul class="further-links">
                            <li><a href="bugs" accesskey="e" tabindex="3">More about bug tracking</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="block odd">
                        <h3>Code hosting and tracking</h3>
                        <h4>Democratise your code.</h4>
                        <p class="screen-holder">
                            <img src="images/home/screens/tracking.jpg" alt="Code hosting and tracking" />
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Bazaar is a distributed version control system that empowers anyone to contribute code to your project. Launchpad provides free hosting of Bazaar branches and an import process that lets people work in Bazaar even if your primary version control system is an older tool such as Subversion or CVS. Launchpad and Bazaar dramatically reduce the barriers to participation in any free software project. 
</p><p>
Launchpad also supports an efficient flow of new code into your project. You can publicly review code and reach consensus with core developers on which new branches are ready to merge into your trunk.
                        </p>
                        <ul class="further-links">
                            <li><a href="branch-hosting-tracking" accesskey="f" tabindex="4">More about code hosting and tracking</a></li>
                            <li><a href="code-review" accesskey="g" tabindex="5">More about code reviews</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="clear"></div>
                </div>
                <div class="furthur-information-block-bot"></div>
            </div>
            <div class="furthur-information-block">
                <div class="furthur-information-block-top"></div>
                <div class="furthur-information-block-mid">
                    <div class="block">
                        <h3>Translations</h3>
                        <h4>Translators shouldn&rsquo;t have to be software engineers.</h4>
                        <p class="screen-holder">
                            <img src="images/home/screens/translations.jpg" alt="Translations" />
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Launchpad&rsquo;s intuitive web interface allows anyone who speaks English and another language as their mother tongue to help translate your project into their language, ready for export in standard GNU GetText files. Putting your project into Launchpad gives you access to 30,000 translators working in 257 languages, with automatic suggestions from a library of more than sixteen million strings.
                        </p>
                        <ul class="further-links">
                            <li><a href="translation" accesskey="h" tabindex="6">More about translations</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="block odd">
                        <h3>Package building and hosting</h3>
                        <h4>Build and host Ubuntu packages in your own apt repository.</h4>
                        <p class="screen-holder">
                            <img src="images/home/screens/hosting.jpg" alt="Package building and hosting" />
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Build and host Ubuntu packages in your own APT repository. Use Launchpad to distribute experimental builds and betas of your software, with automatic updates pushed to your users whenever you modify a package.
                        </p>
                        <ul class="further-links">
                            <li><a href="ppa" accesskey="i" tabindex="7">More about package hosting</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="clear"></div>
                </div>
                <div class="furthur-information-block-bot"></div>
            </div>
            <div class="furthur-information-block">
                <div class="furthur-information-block-top"></div>
                <div class="furthur-information-block-mid">
                    <div class="block">
                        <h3>Blueprint &ndash; specification tracking</h3>
                        <h4>Track new features from idea to implementation.</h4>
                        <p class="screen-holder">
                            <img src="images/home/screens/blueprints.jpg" alt="Blueprint - specification tracking" />
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Target chunks of work to forthcoming releases, see who&rsquo;s working on them and track their progress. Open up your planning: anyone can use Launchpad to register a specification for your project and communicate their progress.
                        </p>
                        <ul class="further-links">
                            <li><a href="feature-tracking" accesskey="j" tabindex="8">More about specification tracking</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="block odd">
                        <h3>Answers &ndash; community support</h3>
                        <h4>Help your users to help themselves.</h4>
                        <p class="screen-holder">
                            <img src="images/home/screens/answers.jpg" alt="Answers - community support" />
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Track help requests just like bug reports. Create FAQs and build a searchable knowledge base of previous answers. When requests for help turn out to be symptoms of an underlying bug, you can easily change the request into a bug report.
                        </p>
                        <ul class="further-links">
                            <li><a href="community-support" accesskey="k" tabindex="9">More about community support</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="clear"></div>
                </div>
